article.description: Mount St. Mary's, Md. 72, St. Francis, N.Y. 54
article.headline: Mount St. Mary's, Md. 72, St. Francis, N.Y. 54
article.linkText: Mount St. Mary's, Md. 72, St. Francis, N.Y. 54
article.story: EMMITSBURG, Md. (AP) -- Five players for Mount St. Mary's scored in double figures to lead the team to a 72-54 victory over St. Francis, N.Y., Thursday night. The Mount (5-11, 4-1 NEC) went on a 17-2 run from the end of the first half to the beginning of the second half to take control of the game. The Terriers (3-14, 1-4) took a 29-21 lead with 4:36 remaining in the first half. Mount St. Mary's opened the second half with five straight points. The Mount extended the lead to 52-41 after a Chris Vann three-pointer with 11:34 before St. Francis rallied to cut the deficit to 57-52 with 6:56 remaining. Mount St. Mary's scored the next 13 points to ensure the win. Mychal Kearse scored 14 points and grabbed nine rebounds for Mount St. Mary's. Jamaal Womack led St. Francis with 16 points.
